<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6a7b193-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s31106"><num value="31106">§ 31106.</num><heading> Exoneration and limitation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The United States is entitled to the exemptions from and limitations of liability provided by law to an owner, charterer, operator, or agent of a vessel.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6a7b194-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s6/c">Pub. L. 109–304, § 6(c)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1522">120 Stat. 1522</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
